# class: repo-map
# schema: path | purpose | owner-role | category
# source: repo walk + per-directory READMEs
# recipe: builtin:repo-structure

backend/ | stateless API tier + DB migrations | backend-engineer | top-level
frontend/ | Angular SPA + design tokens | frontend-engineer | top-level
infrastructure/ | Terraform modules for Azure resources | devops-engineer | top-level
dev_env/ | Docker Compose local-dev stack | devops-engineer | top-level
testing/ | Functional / E2E / smoke / pester | qa-engineer | top-level
docs/ | Architecture doc + ADRs + mockup | solution-architect | top-level
.github/workflows/ | CI pipelines | devops-engineer | nested

# Recipe: per top-level directory + significant nested subtree → one row with
#   path, one-line purpose (from README or inferred), owning cardinal (from
#   local/bindings.md or detected stack), category (top-level | nested).
# Lossless rule: every top-level directory in the repo has a row; nested
#   subtrees only when they carry distinct ownership / purpose from their parent.
# Out of scope: every file. The index is a directory map, not a file inventory.
